.TH "__ip_dev_find" 9 "__ip_dev_find" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ip_dev_find \- find the first device with a given source address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct net_device *" __ip_dev_find
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "__be32 addr "  ","
.BI "bool devref "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
the net namespace
.IP "addr" 12
the source address
.IP "devref" 12
if true, take a reference on the found device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If a caller uses devref=false, it should be protected by RCU, or RTNL
